AB  - The paper develops non-parametric tests for the weak separability or the additive separability of a decision-maker's utility function, given a finite body of price and quantity data. The tests generalize some earlier tests proposed by Afriat and Varian. Blackorby, Primont and Russell have pointed out that the econometric literature on testing separability hypotheses is seriously deficient since the econometric tests tend to impose unwanted restrictions on the parametric functional form in addition to the particular separability hypothesis being tested. Hence, the non-parametric tests in the present paper should serve as useful supplements to the usual econometric tests for separability.
