AB  - The purpose of this paper is to present a new approach to the general equilibrium analysis of economic policy. Our objective is to provide an ordering of alternative economic policies. To this end, we specify measures of social welfare that satisfy the requirements of social choice. A social expenditure function is introduced to translate changes in social welfare based on a social welfare function into money metric social welfare. We decompose money metric social welfare into the sum of money metric equity and money metric efficiency. Finally, we present an evaluation of alternative regulatory policies for natural gas prices in the United States.
